description:
## Location
firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lora_l2.c:590-608

## Finding
The `tx_buf_mutex` is held for the entire duration of `lora_send()`:
```c
k_mutex_lock(&tx_buf_mutex, K_FOREVER);
memcpy(tx_buf, data, len);
int ret = lora_send(lora_state.lora_dev, tx_buf, len);
k_mutex_unlock(&tx_buf_mutex);
```

At SF10/255 bytes, `lora_send()` blocks for ~500ms (documented in comments). This serializes all TX operations.

## What goes wrong
This is **intentional and correct** - the comment explicitly states "the radio can only transmit one packet at a time anyway." The code is clear about this tradeoff.

However, the mutex acquisition uses `K_FOREVER`, meaning a caller blocked waiting for TX can never be interrupted or timed out. If the radio becomes unresponsive during a transmit, all TX threads will block indefinitely.

## Recommendation
Consider using a timeout on tx_buf_mutex acquisition:
```c
int lock_ret = k_mutex_lock(&tx_buf_mutex, K_MSEC(TX_TIMEOUT_MS));
if (lock_ret != 0) {
    return -ETIMEDOUT;
}
```
This would allow callers to implement their own retry/abort logic.
